"{\"uid\": \"aljazeera.com-sports-2024-8-8-nadeem-ends-32-year-wait-for-pakistan-olympic-medal-with-javelin-gold\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Nadeem bags gold with an Olympic record-breaking throw of 92.97m to end Pakistan's 32-year medal drought at the Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 118, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 72, \"end\": 80, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999978120055237, \"rank\": 2.185256861671186e-06, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Save  Share  Pakistan's Arshad Nadeem has madehistoryby clinching the country's first-ever track and field medal at the Olympics as he claimed gold in the men's javelin final in Paris.\", \"from\": 120, \"to\": 304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 133, \"end\": 141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999978120055237, \"rank\": 2.185256861671186e-06, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}, {\"begin\": 298, \"end\": 303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999615179157, \"rank\": 3.8482138452527396e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 27-year-old dethroned defending champion Neeraj Chopra of India and broke the Olympic record at the Stade de France on Thursday.\", \"from\": 306, \"to\": 438, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nadeem threw his arms up in celebration after breaking the Olympic record on his second throw that landed at a stunning 92.97 metres - the best in the world this year.\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 607, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chopra, comfortably ahead in qualifiers and favourite to win, looked off his best form.\", \"from\": 609, \"to\": 696, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His best of 89.45 metres was also his only valid attempt as he fouled on his five other attempts.\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 794, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Grenada's Anderson Peters won bronze with 88.54 metres, a redemptive moment for the two-time world champion after he failed to make it to the final at the Tokyo Games three years ago.\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 796, \"end\": 803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grenada\", \"score\": 0.951518363563411, \"rank\": 0.05095153523745044, \"text\": \"Grenada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grenada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grenada\"}, {\"begin\": 806, \"end\": 821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anderson_Peters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anderson Peters\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anderson_Peters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anderson_Peters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the night belonged to the humble man from Mian Channu, a small town in the eastern Punjab province, who came back from a knee injury early this year and made history for his country despite the dilapidated athletics facilities in the cricket-mad nation.\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 1243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1032, \"end\": 1043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mian_Channu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2872554526814942e-22, \"text\": \"Mian Channu\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mian_Channu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mian_Channu\"}, {\"begin\": 1073, \"end\": 1079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjab\", \"score\": 0.7507492777067608, \"rank\": 0.332002613515155, \"text\": \"Punjab\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjab\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjab\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of Pakistan's eight previous Olympic medals, six came in men's hockey and one each in men's wrestling and boxing.\", \"from\": 1245, \"to\": 1358, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1248, \"end\": 1256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999978120055237, \"rank\": 2.185256861671186e-06, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nadeem's achievement also marked the first medal by Pakistan for eight Olympics, with the last medal coming in 1992 as the men's hockey team won bronze in Barcelona, Spain.\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1532, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1412, \"end\": 1420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999978120055237, \"rank\": 2.185256861671186e-06, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}, {\"begin\": 1515, \"end\": 1524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FC_Barcelona\", \"score\": 0.9999795739009871, \"rank\": 2.042650496103928e-05, \"text\": \"Barcelona\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FC_Barcelona\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FC_Barcelona\"}, {\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998926373395, \"rank\": 1.0713257791599461e-07, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two months before the Olympics, Al Jazeera's Abid Hussain spent a day with Arshad Nadeem as he prepared for the Games.\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 1654, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1568, \"end\": 1578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 0.9999953939333532, \"rank\": 4.604074044506278e-06, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}, {\"begin\": 1581, \"end\": 1593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abid_Hussain\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Abid Hussain\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abid_Hussain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abid_Hussain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Back then, in June, Nadeemtold ushe felt \\\"strong and fit\\\" for the world event, adding he was \\\"quite hopeful of a strong performance in Paris\\\".\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1791, \"end\": 1796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999615179157, \"rank\": 3.8482138452527396e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The world record throw remains with Czechia's Jan Zelezny, who reached a remarkable 98.48, but the new Olympic record, along with the end of a long wait for his country, drew reaction from far and wide from Nadeem's compatriots.\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 2028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1836, \"end\": 1843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9740838450536429, \"rank\": 0.026417692018007862, \"text\": \"Czechia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 2007, \"end\": 2013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadeem_Baig_(actor)\", \"score\": 0.9934085430120708, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nadeem\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadeem_Baig_(actor)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadeem_Baig_(actor)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pakistan men's cricketer Fakhar Zaman said the country was \\\"beaming with pride\\\" in a post on X, while Nadeem's mentor and former coach, Rasheed Ahmad Saqi, was overwhelmed with emotions after his ward won the gold medal.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2250, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2030, \"end\": 2038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999978120055237, \"rank\": 2.185256861671186e-06, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}, {\"begin\": 2055, \"end\": 2067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fakhar_Zaman_(cricketer)\", \"score\": 0.9763313595423369, \"rank\": 0.02424242424242548, \"text\": \"Fakhar Zaman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fakhar_Zaman_(cricketer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fakhar_Zaman_(cricketer)\"}, {\"begin\": 2132, \"end\": 2138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadeem_Baig_(actor)\", \"score\": 0.9934085430120708, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nadeem\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadeem_Baig_(actor)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadeem_Baig_(actor)\"}, {\"begin\": 2174, \"end\": 2179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ahmad\", \"score\": 0.9977623377872882, \"rank\": 0.0021431778451875987, \"text\": \"Ahmad\", \"types\": [\"Q82799\", \"Q202444\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ahmad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ahmad\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is God's miracle and a gift for the entire nation on our independence day next week.\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2342, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am just so proud of Arshad,\\\" he told Al Jazeera moments after the gold medal was confirmed.\", \"from\": 2343, \"to\": 2436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2382, \"end\": 2392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 0.9999953939333532, \"rank\": 4.604074044506278e-06, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Saqi claims he was confident that Nadeem would win a medal and had predicted it would be a gold.\", \"from\": 2438, \"to\": 2534, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I had this belief that he will break some record.\", \"from\": 2536, \"to\": 2586, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was certain he will break his own record or Olympic record and that's what he did.\\\"\", \"from\": 2587, \"to\": 2672, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pakistan's Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif also congratulated Arshad Nadeem on making history for the country.\", \"from\": 2674, \"to\": 2782, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2674, \"end\": 2682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999978120055237, \"rank\": 2.185256861671186e-06, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}, {\"begin\": 2700, \"end\": 2714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shehbaz_Sharif\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shehbaz Sharif\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shehbaz_Sharif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shehbaz_Sharif\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He posted on X: \\\"You have made the whole nation proud.\\\"\", \"from\": 2784, \"to\": 2839, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Al Jazeera English:\", \"from\": 2859, \"to\": 2885, \"entities\": []}]}"